    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.16.41-42_0002"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">42</fw>
                
                <fw type="letterhead">
                Duke University 
                    <lb/>
                <hi rend="caps">DURHAM
                    <lb/>
                NORTH CAROLINA
                    <lb/>
                
                
                DEPARTMENT OF PSYCHOLOGY</hi>
                </fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>December 19, 1935</dateline>
                
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Mr. John <hi rend="caps">G.</hi> Neihardt</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>St. Louis Post Dispatch</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>St. Louis, Mo.</addrLine>
                    </address>
                    
                    <salute>Dear Mr. Neihardt:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>Mrs. Crunden kindly sent me the clipping of your review of my book <hi rend="underline">Extra-Sensory Perception</hi> appearing in the <hi rend="underline">Post-Dispatch</hi>. I want to thank you for this splendid treatment of it and assure you that such a review will do a great deal to aid the work which we are trying to continue here.</p>
                
                <p>I have put your name on the list of those to whom reprints are to be sent and hope that something further will come out of the Duke Para-psychological Laboratory which will be of interest to you.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Sincerely yours,</salute>
                    <signed>JB Rhine</signed>
                    <signed>J. B. Rhine</signed> 
                
                    <note>JBR:MW</note>
                </closer>
                
                <postscript>
                    <p>I enjoy the occasional poem I come across under your name.</p> 
                    <closer><signed>J.B.R.</signed></closer>
                </postscript>
                
                <note type="curatorial">Found in- <hi rend="underline">Extra-Sensory Perception</hi> <hi rend="caps">J.B</hi> Rhine PhD. Bruce Humphries Inc. Boston 1935</note>
                
            </div1>
            
            
            <div1 type="envelope">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.16.41-42_0001"/>
                
                <note type="curatorial">216 Neihardt Collection</note>
                <fw type="curatorial">41</fw>
                
                <ab type="return">
                    <add><hi rend="caps">J. B.</hi> Rhine</add>
                        <lb/>
                    Duke University
                        <lb/>
                    <hi rend="caps">DURHAM, NORTH CAROLINA</hi>
                        <lb/>
                    ------
                        <lb/>
                    Department of Psychology
                </ab>
                
                <ab type="postmark">
                    DURHAM N.C.
                    DEC 30
                    1935
                    11 AM
                    COLLEGE STA.
                </ab>
                <figure>
                    <figDesc>3 Cent Stamp</figDesc>
                    <p>UNITED STATES POST<unclear reason="missing" cert="high">AGE</unclear> WASHINGT<unclear reason="missing" cert="high">ON</unclear> 3 CENT<unclear reason="missing" cert="high">S 3</unclear></p>
                </figure>
                
                <ab type="address">
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Mr. John <hi rend="caps">G.</hi> Neihardt</addrLine>
                        <addrLine><del>St. Louis Post Dispatch</del></addrLine>
                        <addrLine><del>St. Louis, Mo.</del></addrLine>
                        <addrLine><add>Branson, <hi rend="caps">MO</hi></add></addrLine>
                    </address>
                </ab>
                
